1. What is a Segment Tree?

A Segment Tree is a data structure used to efficiently answer range queries and perform updates on an array.

In simple words:
    You have an array
    You want to repeatedly ask questions about a range of elements
    You may also update values

A Segment Tree helps answer these queries much faster than normal methods.

2. The Problem Segment Trees Solve

Suppose we have an array:
arr = [2, 5, 1, 4, 9, 3]

Example Queries:
    Sum from index 1 to 4
    Minimum from 2 to 5
    Maximum from 0 to 3


3. Idea Behind Segment Tree

Instead of calculating the range every time, we store results of segments (ranges) beforehand.

We divide the array into segments:

[0..5]
 /    \
[0..2] [3..5]
 / \     / \
[0..1][2..2][3..4][5..5]

Each node stores information like:

sum, minimum, maximum, gcd etc.
So when a query arrives, we combine results from only relevant nodes.


4. Structure of Segment Tree

Example array:
arr = [2, 5, 1, 4]

Segment tree (for sum):

           [0-3]=12
          /       \
      [0-1]=7     [2-3]=5
      /    \       /   \
 [0]=2   [1]=5  [2]=1 [3]=4

Each node represents:
range -> stored value

| Structure    | Query   | Update  | Use Case         |
| ------------ | ------- | ------- | ---------------- |
| Array        | O(N)    | O(1)    | simple           |
| Prefix Sum   | O(1)    | O(N)    | static arrays    |
| Fenwick Tree | O(logN) | O(logN) | sums             |
| Segment Tree | O(logN) | O(logN) | flexible queries |


Segment Trees support more operations than Fenwick Tree.

Final Intuition

Segment Trees are used when:

Many range queries + updates
They allow you to answer complex queries in logarithmic time.

✅ Short Summary
Segment Tree is:

A binary tree
Stores range information
Supports fast queries and updates

Complexity:
Build: O(N)
Query: O(log N)
Update: O(log N)